                <details class="border rounded-md p-3">
                  <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">
                    Should I use food or supplements to reach my fiber goal?
                  </summary>
                  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    For most people, it is best to get the majority of fiber
                    from <strong>whole foods</strong>—vegetables, fruits,
                    legumes, whole grains, nuts, and seeds—which also provide
                    vitamins, minerals, and phytonutrients. Fiber supplements
                    (like psyllium) can be useful in specific situations, but
                    they should complement, not replace, a balanced diet and
